---
title: Tortelloni with Peas & Bacon in a Creamy Shallot Sauce
description: For this dish, our chefs pulled out a long roster of rockstar ingredients to serve up an incredible 20-minute feat of comforting deliciousness. It starts with tender XL tortelloni that you'll toss in a velvety sauce made with shallot, garlic, chicken stock, and a swirl of rich, tangy sour cream. Add extra-crisp crumbles of bacon and sweet green peas, and you’re instantly transported to a very special, very delicious place we like to call “pasta heaven.”
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/65254c40ca6ba9ab41630380-91f64731.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/65254c40ca6ba9ab41630380.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/tortelloni-with-peas-bacon-65254c40ca6ba9ab41630380
course: main course
cuisine: Southern Europe
time required: 20 minutes
author: Sara Heilman
nutrition:
  calories: 810 kcal
  fat: 48 g
  saturated fat: 20 g
  carbohydrates: 73 g
  sugar: 9 g
  protein: 26 g
  fiber: 6 g
  sodium: 1530 mg
servings: 2
---

Bring a large #pot of salted water to a boil.

Heat a medium dry #pan over medium-high heat. Add @bacon{4%ounce}; cook,
turning occasionally and adjusting heat if browning too quickly, until
crispy, ~{6-10%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer to a paper-towel-lined
#plate. Wipe out pan and let cool slightly.

Once cool enough to handle, roughly chop bacon.

> TIP: While bacon cooks, start prep.

Wash and dry produce.

Halve, peel, and thinly slice @shallot{1}. Peel and mince or grate
@garlic{2%clove}.

Once water is boiling, add @tortelloni{9%ounce} to pot. Cook until tender
and floating to the top, ~{3-4%minutes}.

In the last minute of cooking, add @peas{4%ounce} to pot; cook until peas
are bright green. Reserve 1 cup pasta cooking water (1 1/2 cups for 4 servings),
then drain and return tortelloni and peas to pot.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%teaspoon} in #pan used for bacon over medium
heat. Add shallot and garlic; cook, stirring, until softened and lightly
browned, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir in @chicken stock concentrate{1} and ½ cup reserved pasta cooking water
(1 cup for 4 servings).

Bring to a simmer and cook until slightly thickened, ~{30-60%seconds}.

> TIP: If your pasta isn't done cooking yet, ladle pasta water directly from pot.

Turn off heat; whisk in @sour cream{3%tablespoon} and @cream cheese{2%tablespoon}
until well combined. Season with @pepper{}.

To pot with drained tortelloni and peas, add chopped bacon and shallot
sauce; stir to combine. If needed, add splashes of reserved pasta cooking
water until everything is coated in a creamy sauce.

Divide tortelloni between shallow #bowls{} and serve.

> Bacon is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.